### Spring Data JPA

Spring Data JPA reduces boilerplate data access code. By extending `JpaRepository`, your interface automatically inherits CRUD operations and more.

### JpaRepository Interface

```java
public interface UserRepository extends JpaRepository<User, Long> {
    // Inherits: save(), findById(), findAll(), count(), deleteById(), etc.
}
```

### Query Derivation

Spring Data JPA derives queries from method names. No implementation needed.

```java
public interface UserRepository extends JpaRepository<User, Long> {
    Optional<User> findByEmail(String email);
    List<User> findByLastNameAndFirstName(String lastName, String firstName);
    List<User> findByAgeGreaterThan(int age);
    List<User> findByActiveTrueOrderByCreatedAtDesc();
    List<User> findByDepartmentName(String departmentName);
}
```

### @Query for Custom JPQL

Use `@Query` when method naming becomes unwieldy or for complex queries.

```java
public interface UserRepository extends JpaRepository<User, Long> {
    @Query("SELECT u FROM User u WHERE u.email = :email")
    Optional<User> findByEmailCustom(@Param("email") String email);

    @Query("SELECT u FROM User u WHERE u.lastName LIKE %:search% OR u.firstName LIKE %:search%")
    List<User> searchByName(@Param("search") String search);
}
```

